docs.text: topless women talk about their lives falls into that category that i mentioned in the devil's advocate : movies that have a brilliant beginning but don't know how to end .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it begins by introducing us to a selection of characters who all know each other .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: there is liz , who oversleeps and so is running late for her appointment , prue who is getting married , geoff , liz's boyfriend , neil , her previous boyfriend , ant who has written a screenplay .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: for the first hour , we get to know these people through everyday activities , as they talk on the phone , go out to dinner , hang clothes on the line .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the interactions seem so truthful and guileless that it is almost as if the film-makers hid cameras around the place and filmed these people unbeknownst to them .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: at times , the events border on the ridiculous , like the screening of the film , but they still seem in keeping with the characters and their lives .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: this doesn't sound like a brilliant premise for a film - " we just follow a lot of people around who are vaguely related " - but it's the execution of the idea that makes topless women talk about their lives so engrossing .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: unfortunately this level of honesty isn't maintained .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: with about half an hour to go , a sense of impending doom invades topless women talk about their lives and from there is descends into melodrama .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: such a disappointment after such a brilliant start .

docs.text: the actors are all quite good with ms . danielle cormack as liz being particularly impressive .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the energy of her character is palpable and is a major reason the movie is so watchable .

docs.text: a lot of the performances are a bit rough around the edges but this suits totally the documentary feel of the film .

docs.text: that is why the melodramatic turn of events comes as such a shock .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: up till that point , i was transported to this world where these real but mildly insane events were taking place .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: while the final half hour is not beyond the realms of possibility , it's unlikely in a way that is jarring to someone caught up in the world of the film .
